Reasoning: The paper proposes two novel deep learning-based models for predicting smartphone users' location with WiFi fingerprints. This involves combining convolutional neural networks, recurrent neural networks, and mixture density networks, which are all techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
